Dashboard coding standards

- Server components by default. Client components only for state, browser APIs, drag/drop, forms, or interactivity.
- Type every boundary. Use existing Supabase generated types.
- Reuse existing UI primitives and Tailwind patterns before creating new ones.
- Keep DB logic in lib/db/* and business logic out of JSX.
- No new dependencies without approval.
- Do not refactor unrelated files. If scope expands, stop and ask.
- New code must not introduce lint or type errors.
